Which of the following is a correct definition of a class?
a) An instance of an object
b) A blueprint or prototype for creating objects
c) A method in Java
d) A package in Java
Answer : b
 What are the main components of a class?
a) Attributes and Packages
b) Objects and References
c) Methods and Attributes
d) Constructors and Destructors
Answer : c
What is an object in Java?
a) A reference to a class
b) A runtime entity
c) A method
d) An attribute
Answer : b
Which keyword is used to create a new instance of a class?
a) new
b) this
c) instance
d) object
Answer : a
What do we mean by the "state" of an object?
a) Its behavior
b) The values assigned to its instance variables
c) Its methods
d) Its interface
Answer : b
